title: 144E.286 EXAMINER QUALIFICATIONS FOR EMERGENCY MEDICAL TECHNICIAN TESTING.
text:
MS 2002 [Repealed, 2004 c 144 s 9]
MS 2002 [Repealed, 2004 c 144 s 9]
An examiner testing EMT, AEMT, or paramedic practical skills must be certified at or above the level the examiner is testing or must be a registered nurse, physician, or physician assistant familiar with current out-of-hospital care. A physician must be available to answer questions relating to the evaluation of skill performance at the AEMT and paramedic practical examination.
